---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="Terms of Service" activePage="" description="Purple Directive terms of service — terms governing your use of our website, products, and consulting services.">

  <section class="legal-page">
    <h1>Terms of Service</h1>
    <p class="legal-updated">Last updated: March 24, 2026</p>

    <p>
      These terms govern your use of purpledirective.com and any products or services
      offered by Purple Directive LLC ("we", "us", "our"). By using our site or purchasing
      our products, you agree to these terms.
    </p>

    <h2>Products — Digital Downloads</h2>

    <h3>License</h3>
    <p>
      When you purchase a digital product (e.g., the SOP Template Bundle), you receive a
      non-exclusive, non-transferable license to use, modify, and implement the templates
      within your organization. You may customize the templates with your branding,
      personnel, and procedures.
    </p>

    <h3>Restrictions</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>You may not resell, redistribute, or sublicense the templates as-is or as a competing product</li>
      <li>You may not claim authorship of the original templates</li>
      <li>You may share completed (customized, site-specific) SOPs within your organization and with sponsors, CROs, or IRBs as part of normal clinical operations</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Delivery</h3>
    <p>
      Digital products are delivered via email immediately after purchase. The download
      link does not expire. If you do not receive your download within 15 minutes,
      check your spam folder and contact
      <a href="mailto:info@purpledirective.com">info@purpledirective.com</a>.
    </p>

    <h3>Refund Policy</h3>
    <p>
      Due to the digital nature of our products, all sales are final. If you experience a
      technical issue that prevents you from accessing your purchase, contact us and we
      will resolve it promptly. If we are unable to deliver the product, we will issue a
      full refund.
    </p>

    <h2>Consulting Services</h2>
    <p>
      Consulting engagements are governed by separate statements of work (SOW) agreed upon
      before work begins. Consulting fees, deliverables, timelines, and confidentiality
      terms are defined in each SOW.
    </p>

    <h2>Disclaimer</h2>
    <p>
      Our products and services are provided for informational and operational purposes only.
      They do not constitute legal, regulatory, or medical advice. SOP templates are
      customizable starting points and must be reviewed, adapted, and validated against
      your institution's specific policies, applicable regulations (including ICH E6(R2/R3),
      21 CFR Parts 11/50/56/312, and 45 CFR Part 46), IRB requirements, and sponsor
      protocols before implementation.
    </p>
    <p>
      Purple Directive LLC assumes no liability for the use or misuse of any product
      or service. You are responsible for ensuring that any materials derived from our
      templates comply with your regulatory environment.
    </p>

    <h2>Intellectual Property</h2>
    <p>
      All content on purpledirective.com — including text, design, logos, and code — is
      the property of Purple Directive LLC unless otherwise noted. Open-source projects
      published on our GitHub are governed by their respective licenses.
    </p>

    <h2>Limitation of Liability</h2>
    <p>
      To the maximum extent permitted by law, Purple Directive LLC shall not be liable for
      any indirect, incidental, special, consequential, or punitive damages arising from
      your use of our products or services, regardless of the cause of action.
    </p>
    <p>
      Our total liability for any claim related to a product purchase shall not exceed the
      amount you paid for that product.
    </p>

    <h2>Governing Law</h2>
    <p>
      These terms are governed by the laws of the State of New York, without regard to
      conflict of law provisions.
    </p>

    <h2>Changes to These Terms</h2>
    <p>
      We may update these terms from time to time. Changes will be posted on this page
      with an updated date. Continued use of the site after changes constitutes acceptance.
    </p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>
      Questions about these terms? Email us at
      <a href="mailto:info@purpledirective.com">info@purpledirective.com</a>.
    </p>
  </section>

</Base>

<style>
  .legal-page {
    max-width: 680px;
    padding: var(--spacing-xl) 0;
  }

  .legal-page h1 {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-xs);
  }

  .legal-updated {
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-xl);
  }

  .legal-page h2 {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    margin-top: var(--spacing-xl);
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-sm);
    padding-top: var(--spacing-md);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .legal-page h2:first-of-type {
    border-top: none;
    padding-top: 0;
  }

  .legal-page h3 {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    margin-top: var(--spacing-md);
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-xs);
  }

  .legal-page p,
  .legal-page li {
    font-size: 0.88rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .legal-page ul {
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
    margin: var(--spacing-sm) 0;
  }

  .legal-page li {
    margin-bottom: 0.3rem;
  }

  .legal-page a {
    color: var(--purple-primary);
  }
</style>
